Business Brief -- Southland Corp.:
   Interest Payment to Banks
   Of $12.2 Million Is Ordered
Southland first failed to make interest payments on its
some of its bonds in June 1990, but it never paid the
increased interest rate. The bank group is led by Citibank,
Bankers Trust, Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce,
Manufacturers Hanover and Security Pacific.
   A Southland spokeswoman said the company was surprised and
disappointed by the ruling and is weighing its options.